New Zealand Retail sales by region (2012)

Victor

3 octobre 2018

Packages used:

library(topogram)
library(sf)
## Linking to GEOS 3.6.1, GDAL 2.2.3, proj.4 4.9.3
library(rmapshaper)

Retail data

Data came from Stats NZ. You can download shapes here, select export shapefile with WGS 84 projection.

# read {sf} object
nz_retail <- read_sf("datas/retail-trade-sales-per-capita-by-region-2012-2017.shp")
# simplify geometries
nz_retail <- ms_simplify(nz_retail)

Cartogram

topogram(
  shape = nz_retail,
  value = c("Per_capita", "Per_capi_1", "Per_capi_2", "Per_capi_3",
            "Per_capi_4", "Per_capi_5", "Total_trad", "Total_tr_1", "Total_tr_2",
            "Total_tr_3"),
  tooltip_label = ~REGC2018_V, 
  format_value = ",.0f",
  n_iteration = 20
)%>% add_legend(
  title = "",
  title_width = 200,
  orientation = "vertical",
  label_format = ".2s"
)
